t into a vehicle for profound theatrical and philosophical experience, was a brilliant actor himself, and his treatises touch on every aspect of the theater of his time. His theories, mixing philosophical and practical insights, often seem strikingly contemporary. Since their discovery early in this century. these secret treatises have been considered among the most valuable and representative documents in the history of Japanese aesthetics. They discuss subjects from the art of the playwright to the reciprocal nature of the relationship between performer and audience.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Theater / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aAmaterasu.  aAshikawa Yoshimitsu.  aBook of Documents.  aBroad Mastery.  aConfucius and the Analects.  aDelicacy within Strength.  aExternalization.  aFascination.  aFlower of Tranquillity.  aFulfillment.  aGrace.  aHighest Fruition.  aJinen Koji.  aKan'ami.  aKiami.  aMagnitude.  aNan'ami.  aOn'ami.  aPeerless Charm.  aPerfect Fluency.  aRole Playing.  aShiki samban.  aThree Role Types.  aTwo Basic Arts.  aYamato sarugaku.  adengaku.  ahayabushi.  aissei.  akusemai.  arenga.  asashigoe.  atachiai.1 aChappell, Wallace, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMasakazu, Yamazaki, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMotoyoshi, Hata No, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRimer, J. Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRimer, J. Thomas.1 aYamazaki, Masakazu, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Archive (pre 2000) eBook Packagez978311064968008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPr